tratification, and health inequality that are woven into the health care taught and provided at AIIMS, asking what is lost when medicine is used not as a social equalizer but as a means to cultivate and maintain prestige.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Jan 2022) 0aMedical educationzIndia. 0aOccupational prestigezIndia. 0aSocial medicinezIndia. 0aTeaching hospitalszIndia. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Disease & Health Issues.2bisacsh  aAIIMS.  aIndia.  aaffirmative action.  aanthropology.  adoctors.  ahealth systems.  ahigher education.  ainequalities.  amedical education.  ayoung people.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073914540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362826740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503628267423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503628267/original  a978-3-11-073914-5  Stanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles